
// This Hyperlambda code snippet demonstrates how to set a cache item using the [cache.set] slot. It retrieves the cache key, value, and expiration time in seconds from the [.arguments] node, using [get-value] to extract these values. The cache item is then stored with the specified key and will expire after the given number of seconds. The slots used are: [cache.set] for setting the cache item, [get-value] for retrieving argument values, and [expiration] for setting the cache duration.
cache.set:x:@.arguments/*/key
   get-value:x:@.arguments/*/value
   expiration:x:@.arguments/*/seconds
